	 <para>
		On the host system, make a location where the downloaded ISO can be stored: 
<screen>
&srvprompt; <userinput>mkdir /var/isos</userinput></screen>
		 <itemizedlist>
			<listitem>
				<para>
					Download the Fedora 18 DVD, see <ulink url="http://download.fedoraproject.org/pub/fedora/linux/releases/18/Fedora/x86_64/iso/Fedora-18-x86_64-DVD.iso">Download Fedora 18</ulink> and store it in <filename class="directory">/var/isos</filename>.
				</para>

			</listitem>

		</itemizedlist>
		 After the download, our <filename class="directory">/var/isos</filename> is: 
<screen>
&srvprompt; <userinput>ls -l /var/isos | grep Fedora-18</userinput>
-rw-------. 1 qemu qemu 4573888512 Jan 15 20:30 Fedora-18-x86_64-DVD.iso
</screen>

